# Bolshaya Rechka, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Bolshaya Rechka () is a rural locality (a selo) in Kabansky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 494 as of 2010. There are 4 streets.
Geography
Bolshaya Rechka is located  southwest of Kabansk (the district's administrative centre) by road. Posolskaya is the nearest rural locality.
